<chapter xml:id="ch-sim-and-diag" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Similarity and Diagonalisation</title>

  <introduction>
   <p>
Diagonal matrices have many nice properties. For example, two diagonal matrices can be multiplied 
simply by multiplying the corresponding diagonal elements. In this chapter, we explain how to 
convert a matrix into a diagonal one, and discuss when this is possible.
</p>
